text: Kami ada acara di gedung pertemuan besar di sebelah timur Hotel Sutasoma selama 3 hari-2 malam berturutan, sehingga menginap di hotel ini selama 2 malam. Oleh karena itu saya jadi mengetahui bahwa walaupun berada di dalam satu kompleks yang sama, tetapi tidak ada akses langsung dari hotel ke gedung pertemuan. Saya harus keluar hotel dulu baru kemudian dapat akses ke gedung pertemuannya. Ini hal yang tidak lazim dan membuat tidak nyaman. Servis hotelnya sendiri memenuhi standar sebuah hotel bisnis. Proses check-in dan check-out lancar. Akses ke kamar juga mudah, serta ukuran kamar memadai sebagai urban business hotel. Pilihan sarapan standar saja, sedangkan pada waktu makan lainnya kami memilih mencari makan yang banyak tersedia di sekitar hotel.

text: We stayed at Sutasoma Hotel from 15 - 22 March 2023 in room 525. We absolutely loved our stay. We arrived before check-in time so we were given welcome drinks in the restaurant whilst they prepared a room for us. By 11am, we were assigned room 525. The room looked out onto The Tribrata Darmawangsa and The Opus Grand Ballroom, which are beautiful buildings in their own right (we were also very lucky to see a couple of special weddings which had a visit of the President to one of them). Our room was spacious, bed was very comfortable, and the pillows were great. The room is on the opposite side to a local mosque, so it shielded us from the call to prayer (you could still hear it but it was negligible). The hotel is about 300m from Blok A MRT station stop, which you can use to go into central Jakarta. There's a rooftop cafe across from the hotel, called Pain De Mie, but we only went there once as the breakfast buffet more than catered to our needs - highly recommend you include this option when booking a room. As part of breakfast, you can have eggs/noodles cooked to your choice, and there's pastries available. The hotel is about a 10 minute walk from a lovely restaurant called the Plataron Dharmawangsa, it's a must visit - the decor/ambience is gorgeous and the food delicious. I digress, getting back to the hotel. The staff were amazing and always on hand to offer assistance to make our stay a wonderful experience. Be sure to install the Grab app as it's the primary way to get around Jakarta, and if you're a foreigner, the cost is minimal - had to get used to the conversion rate. Take a look at the photos I've included. When staying at Sutasoma, you feel like living in a lap of luxury.
title: Grandiuer stay in South Jakarta

title: Birthday Staycation

text:
I had a wonderful time staying at Sutasoma Hotel. I never heard this hotel before, so I had no high expectation. 

Surprisingly, the hotel was very nice. Located strategically in South Jakarta, you have plenty of culinary options nearby (from Blok M area, Fatmawati, or you can go to Pondok Indah). And if you wish to travel using public transportation, there is a MRT Station within walking distance. 

So my stay was a family stay, not business. This hotel is not exclusively hotel for family or business, but the management offered activities for my son. They provided crayons, paper to color, balloons, and small toys. My son reacted positively to this. 

The room is quite spacious and the amenities were great. But, the room could have better sound proofing. I notice that sound of water from the pipe was quite (from other room) easy to detect and a bit annoying. 

The breakfast buffet was good. But if, there is a formal meeting at the Tribrata (which located next door), you'll find difficulty finding seats. Perhaps the management could opted for smaller but still convenient desk and chairs to maximize capacity. Currently, they use big sofas. It's comfortable for sitting, but you have to bend a bit for dining. 

The hotel needs to improve the gym as most of the equipment were not working when I stayed there. 

Another possible upgrade was the parking space. Limited parking space available for the hotel, though you can park safely at the basement of Tribrata ballroom. When I stayed it was raining and windy most of the time, and the access from basement to lobby was not covered by ceilings. Perhaps in the future it could be installed to prevent us from getting wet. 

Last but not least, I find that the price for this 4 star hotel is reasonable. And they really care for hygiene (at least on paper they claimed they sanitize every day and the room will be used only after 48 hours from the last visitor). 

All in all, great value, great experience, wonderful hospitality. Thank you, Sutasoma!
title: Pleasantly surprised

text:
Stayed for 4 nights here after 3 years of pandemic travel restrictions. Everything was perfect! The room was clean, the most important for me: the room temperature was excellent and cool (air conditioner was working very well!).

The hotel is located in the very nice area of South Jakarta,  easy access to other places in Jakarta. 300 m there is a PCR test center, accross there is Korean supermarket and next door are bunch of Banks if you want to do business not only leisure

I ordered room service and the food was also very yummy and well made! I just wished that the hotel have more menu to choose from.

Will definitely comeback to stay!

I was recommended to this hotel by a friend. Went there during the Eid holiday wanting to have a self-care day for myself, and I was not disappointed. 
First of all, upon entering, I was delighted by the Pokemon-themed amenities in my room. They did their research very well to make their guest feel special. The room was comfortable, nicely air-conditioned (even too cold at times but I was not complaining). Breakfast selection was decent, and also understandable as we're still in pandemic. The bubur ayam was excellent but missing cakwe, which is the best part of any bubur.
My suggestion would be to change the body shower/body lotion bottle because it was so hard to squeeze, I ended up opening the entire cap to get the soap out.

Overall, I will still recommend this hotel to anyone who'd like to have a quiet stay in town.

text: Went there with friends for Iftar at their Quba Restaurant. The food variety was diverse, great taste - loved their sop buntut, great ambience. They also have an outdoor space hence giving a rooftop vibe. Would love to visit again.

text:

We came with family, the place it's amazing, very nice view, staff very helpful,food is amazing, there is cake shop at lobby we buy bread and cake with 30%, recommended hotel for staycation.

text: We were come for breakfasting on April  21,2021,the location at 8th floor outdoor,amazing city view, very nice staff, many variety of Indonesian and middle east food was fantastic,recommended for social event and wedding, definitely come back again. Thank you
title: Fantastic Quba Restaurant

text:
On April 30, we held Iftar with friends in Quba,  we have been warmly welcomed by security from the moment we entered the Sutasoma hotel area, without ignoring health protocols and security procedure. 
When we arrived at Quba Resto,  our eyes were spoiled with an amazing atmosphere, the view of the capital city building lights, the warm and friendly service of the employees, made us feel comfortable and special and also I will not forget that all the food are very delicious especially the oxtail soup.
title: Iftar in Quba pop up Resto

text:
Its a new hotel but rightly so as all the facilities was crisp, clean and functioning. The room was immaculate with wide screen TV and a 2x2 comfortable bed and pillows. The window bench is a very good addition which you dont get many in a business hotel.
The food was excellent. Tried burger, perfect patty and its curly fries was to die for!!! 
The lounge, Atman Lounge serve the best black coffee (no sugar no milk, just black - perfect) with cozy ambiance.
To top it up....the staff was great..friendly and attentive. Fajri and Helmi in concierge were both very helpful. Great location as well in a "trendy capital" in South Jakarta 😁

Overall....one of the best value for money staycation in JKT
title: Wonderful staycation

text: Brand New Hotel hotel at south jakarta located in Darmawangsa main Road, with modern interior design, friendly staff, breakfast taste is delicious, gym and pool facilites we use at the hotel. Free parking and frii wifi at the hotel. Thank You Sutasoma Hotel Keep it Up
title: Modern New Hotel @South Jakarta

photos.caption: New hotel at south Jakarta, Modern Design, friendly staff, breakfast is good, Amazing

text: Overall the hotel location is very strategical at south jakarta, the service is excellent  and the room is very cozy. The restaurant serving delicious home made indonesian taste. I also experienced breakfasting at Quba pop-resto, the food also great and delicious
title: Great hotel with great food

text: It was my first time came for Iftar dinner with friends at Quba. The ambience was very good as it is on the rooftop. So much variety of delicious foods and with these great staff so helpful. Me and friends may be come back for the second time.
title: Iftar Gathering at Quba

text: Frankly speaking, this is the first time diner with friends, with this semi-outdoor place, it is highly recommended if anyone wants to come here.  the food served is also delicious and especially the health protocol is also good
title: Dinner meeting

text: I came to Quba twice during this Ramadan to break the fasting. Both were with my collegues. And I really want to come for my third time but it's already full booked. I do really love the food. This place has plenty of food and it's all delicious. Sop buntut, empal gentong, satay, lontong cap gomeh, siomay, sharma, laksa singapore, mie ayam bakso, you name it. Teh tarik and coffee also good. And the price is incredible. Super worthy. Only 250k nett. You won't find the place like this on 4-5stars hotels. Please... Make it regularly.
title: Quba Pop Up Restaurant

text: This is the 2nd time I came to this hotel & I enjoyed their food & service. First time I had my late lunch at Atman Lounge. The server, Bishri if i remember correctly, was polite & helpful. He speaks good English too btw. Second one was just last week to try their iftar all you can eat with my dad. So worth it. My dad is so happy he took the oxtail soup 3 times. Surely will come again.
title: Nice food, nice place

text:

text: 年末年始に休暇で利用する宿泊客で混んでいたにもかかわらずスタッフの方々のおもてなし、サービスはとても行き届いていたので大変満喫出来ました。是非また宿泊したいと思いました。ホテルのお部屋はとても綺麗で、設備も特に問題なく快適に過ごせました。特にコンプリメントのミネラルウォーターはどこかの山から汲んできた新鮮なお水との事で美味しく頂けました。
